:''See also'' [[Termite]]
==English==

===Etymology===
[[Back-formation]] ''termites'' was the three-syllable plural of ''termes'' but the singular was lost, the plural given two syllables, and now we have ''termite'' and ''termites''.
From Latin termes, as in 'terminal', meaning those that terminate, or destroy.

===Noun===
'''termite''' (''plural'' '''termites''')
#a white bodied, [[wood]] consuming [[insect]] of the [[order]] ''Isoptera''.

